cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the degree of decentralization in blockchain systems, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also analyzes the process of stake-weighted election of witnesses in the DPoS consensus protocol, which involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents a comparison study of two different consensus protocols, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
